'''''Star Wars'' 7''' is the seventh issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was co-written by [[Roy Thomas]] and [[Howard Chaykin]], with art by Chaykin and [[Frank Springer]], and it was first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[October 11]], [[1977]]. The issue features the story "'''New Planets, New Perils!'''," which was the series' first story set after the events of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

==Publisher's summary==
''Han and Chewie head out to pay their debt to Jabba, when they're attacked by pirates!''

==Plot summary==
After bidding farewell to their [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] friends, Han Solo and Chewbacca set out to return to [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] to pay off their debt to Jabba the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. En route, they are hijacked by space pirate [[Crimson Jack/Legends|Crimson Jack]] and his gang of thugs. The pirates take the reward [[Currency/Legends|money]] given to Han and Chewbacca by the Rebel Alliance for [[Rescue of Princess Leia/Legends|rescuing]] [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] but spare their lives.

Forced to lay low because they cannot pay Jabba, the two seek refuge on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Aduba-3/Legends|Aduba-3]]. There they are hired by [[Pera]], a [[Priest/Legends|priest]] of the [[Sacred Way/Legends|Sacred Way]], to bury a recently deceased [[Cyborg/Legends|borg]]. Although they meet with some resistance from the locals who object to having a borg buried in their traditional mound, they do eventually find their way to the burial site. After completing that task, the two smugglers are relaxing in a local [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]], where they are presented with a much deadlier job.

==Development==
The issue had a shipping date of [[September 13]], [[1977]],<ref name="Year By Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> an on-sale date of [[October 11]], 1977, and a [[January]] [[1978]] cover date.<ref name="Marvel" />

==Continuity==
''Star Wars'' 7 features the story "New Planets, New Perils!," which was one of the first installments of what eventually became the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]].<ref name="Year By Year" /> It introduces the characters Crimson Jack and [[Jolli]], who are recurring characters in the [[Star Wars (1977)|series]].<ref name="Star Wars 11">[[Star Wars (1977) 11|''Star Wars'' (1977) 11]]</ref><ref name="Star Wars 12">[[Star Wars (1977) 12|''Star Wars'' (1977) 12]]</ref>

In [[The Rebel Thief]] Han claims he has returned his award money back to the Rebels. This, however, contradicts this comic issue, where it was stolen by [[Crimson Jack/Legends|Crimson Jack]].

